reviewText: Loved this movie! Anyone with an interest in tattooing should see this! Great stories!
I'm so happy I came across this short film. Stoney was one of a kind no doubt about it. You won't be disappointed with this film!!

Amazing but short look into the life and career of Leonard St. Clair. The biggest highlight is the way it shows how he was more than a prolific artist and tattooer, but as a great person with a fun outlook.
Short little film. Simple, quirky, charming. Loved it.

He was one of the best. Stoney Knows How is an account of the tattoo world told through the eyes of a crippled circus man and what he saw and went through. Worth a watch by tattooers and collectors alike.
Stoney Knows How Stoney talks about his snake sideshow, and other snake stories, with Ed Hardy.
